    "title": "Pronouns y and en",
    "explanation": "Avril va à la fête. Il y a de la suie. — the word y often means 'there' or replaces à + [place]. Avril y va = Avril goes THERE.\n\nNotice en: il en a (he has SOME of it). En replaces de + [thing].\n\nRe-read and find every y and en. What place or thing does each one replace?"
